OL,6,FMs Donelan told the committee: "While
OL,7,FI always err on the side of
OL,8,Ftransparency, I am now clear that in
OL,9,Fthis case, I could have sent the
OL,10,Fletter in confidence to the UKRI in
OL,11,Forder for them to undertake the
OL,12,Finvestigations privately.
OL,14,F"And I do apologise for not having
OL,15,Fdone so, and for any distraction that
OL,16,Fthis decision has caused from this
OL,17,FGovernment's positive agenda."
